cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use HPO Explorer in your work, please cite it as below."
title: "HPO Explorer"
abstract: >-
  A free, privacy-preserving web application that pairs an interactive Human
  Phenotype Ontology browser with a client-side clinical-note-to-HPO extractor
  (lexical + in-browser semantic matching, negation/family/uncertainty modeling,
  and annotation-frequency Information-Content weighting), with built-in
  phenotypic similarity, disease matching, and gene prioritization.
type: software
authors:
